# OpenIM line-ending policy.
#
# Scope: the agentINVEST launcher/script class and the dbt source that is
# executed/read INSIDE WSL2. These files must materialise with LF on every
# checkout regardless of the operator's core.autocrlf — a CRLF-materialised
# *.sh aborts WSL bash at `set -euo pipefail` (exit 2), which broke
# `pnpm dbt:build` / `agentinvest-cli seed` / the `bootstrap` data-half on a
# fresh Windows checkout. This is deliberately TARGETED, not a repo-wide
# `* text=auto`: the model markdown, docs, and host-side files keep the
# operator's native line-ending behaviour (no repo-wide churn).

# --- launcher/script class (the breaking surface + its same-class radius) ---
*.sh   text eol=lf
*.mjs  text eol=lf

# --- the dbt + config + canonical-model source executed/read inside WSL2 (reference/ only) ---
# dbt + the Python/uv toolchain read these under WSL2; pinning LF keeps the whole
# WSL-executed agentINVEST surface line-ending-consistent and forecloses the next
# latent CRLF case in the same execution context. Path-scoped so nothing outside
# reference/ (e.g. model/docs YAML) is touched. The *.py + *.csv lines were added
# when the canonical-model package + dbt entity seeds (read by the WSL2-side
# uv/dbt toolchain) landed — same rationale as the dbt source.
reference/**/*.sql  text eol=lf
reference/**/*.yml  text eol=lf
reference/**/*.toml text eol=lf
reference/**/*.py   text eol=lf
reference/**/*.csv  text eol=lf
# JSON seeds/oracle (e.g. break_labels.json) the generator writes LF — keep eol=lf so
# a regenerate stays byte-stable and the pipeline stays idempotent (the .csv rationale).
reference/**/*.json text eol=lf
